# .git-leak-blocklist  —  per-fork operator leak-detection blocklist.
#
# Copy this file to .git-leak-blocklist (gitignored, NOT committed) and
# populate with the strings that uniquely identify YOUR network and YOUR
# household. The leak detector (tools/leak_detector.py, Layer E) does a
# case-insensitive substring match for each literal entry and a regex
# match for each line prefixed with `re:`.
#
# What to put here
# ----------------
#   - your real first/last name and any common spellings or initials
#   - your street name (full and partial — "Wagon Wheel" not just "23 Wagon
#     Wheel" — because partial matches are still identifying)
#   - other household members' first names if they appear in device labels
#   - pet names if they appear in device labels (Lutron labels, etc.)
#   - your real domain names (the public ones you own)
#   - any third-party-installer business names tied to your address
#   - real device labels you've used in your UniFi controller that are
#     unusual enough to be identifying ("23 Wagon Wheel Doorbell Cam")
#   - the OUI prefixes of devices you actually own when paired with
#     non-zeroed suffixes (regex form: `re:^60:64:05:[^0]`)
#   - real network MAC addresses you've seen in your snapshots
#
# What NOT to put here
# --------------------
#   - generic words ("camera", "doorbell") — those produce too many false
#     positives in legitimate code/tests
#   - public-knowledge things (your city, your ISP) — not a leak per se
#
# Examples (replace with YOUR real values, then the file becomes private)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Real names + identifiers
# YourFirstName
# YourLastName
# yourusername
#
# Partial street name
# Wagon Wheel
#
# Household member names that appear in device labels
# Lily
# Sarah
#
# Real domains
# according-to-plan.com
# yourcompany.io
#
# Real device labels from your UniFi controller
# 23 Wagon Wheel Doorbell Cam
# Master Bedroom AP
#
# Real MACs (full literal, lowercase preferred)
# 60:64:05:6c:89:5a
# ec:b5:fa:33:98:f1
# b0:b9:8a:44:da:2c
#
# Regex patterns for OUI + non-zeroed-suffix combinations
# re:^60:64:05:(?!00:00:)
# re:^ec:b5:fa:(?!00:00:)
